      "note": "The expression suradiq - rendered by me as \"billowing folds\" - literally denotes an awning or the outer covering of a tent, and alludes here to the billowing \"walls of smoke\" that will surround the sinners (Zamakhshari): a symbolism meant to stress the inescapability of their suffering in the hereafter (Razi)."
